                            <comment id="13490574" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 5 Nov 2012 11:19:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching trivial patch to fix the limitation introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4612&quot; title=&quot;cql error with ORDER BY when using IN&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4612&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4612&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I.e. it doesn&apos;t force the order by columns to be select, unless this is an IN query. I&apos;ve opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4911&quot; title=&quot;Lift limitation that order by columns must be selected for IN queries&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4911&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4911&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to remove the limitation for IN queries, but that part has never worked anyway so it&apos;s more of an improvement.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13490687" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 5 Nov 2012 15:28:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13490704" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 5 Nov 2012 16:06:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
